cdx6500PPCTdot3PortTable.name: cdx6500PPCTdot3PortTable
cdx6500PPCTdot3PortTable.description: This table contains Ethernet interface parameters and state variables, one entry per 802.3 interface.

cdx6500PPCTdot3PortEntry.name: cdx6500PPCTdot3PortEntry
cdx6500PPCTdot3PortEntry.description: A list of Ethernet status and parameter values for an 802.3 interface.

cdx6500dot3IfIndex.name: cdx6500dot3IfIndex
cdx6500dot3IfIndex.description: This object is the port number for the Interface.

cdx6500dot3LanCableType.name: cdx6500dot3LanCableType
cdx6500dot3LanCableType.description: Two LAN connectors are provided and only one connector, selected by software, is active at any given time. This parameter specifies the type of cable and therefore which connector is used for the LAN interface as follows: utp: Unshielded Twisted Pair (RJ-45) aui: Attachment Unit Interface (DB-15)

cdx6500dot3PortMacAddress.name: cdx6500dot3PortMacAddress
cdx6500dot3PortMacAddress.description: Specifies the MAC address of the LAN port. The entered value of 00-00-00-00-00-00 will be replaced by the Burned In Address (BIA) if the LAN hardware is present.

cdx6500dot3TransmitQueueLimit.name: cdx6500dot3TransmitQueueLimit
cdx6500dot3TransmitQueueLimit.description: Number of frames that can be queued on the LAN transmitter before any frame is dropped.

cdx6500dot3CollisionSensitivity.name: cdx6500dot3CollisionSensitivity
cdx6500dot3CollisionSensitivity.description: This parameter specifies the width required of the collision detection signal, in bit times, before it is recognized that a collision has occurred.

cdx6500dot3CarrierSensitivity.name: cdx6500dot3CarrierSensitivity
cdx6500dot3CarrierSensitivity.description: This parameter specifies the width required of the carrier sense signal in bit times, before it is recognized as being active. Carrier sense deactivation is recognized immediately. This capability is useful in noisy cable environments.

cdx6500dot3BridgeLinkNum.name: cdx6500dot3BridgeLinkNum
cdx6500dot3BridgeLinkNum.description: This parameter specifies the bridge link number associated with this LAN port.

cdx6500dot3RouterIfNum.name: cdx6500dot3RouterIfNum
cdx6500dot3RouterIfNum.description: This parameter specifies the router interface number associated with this LAN port.

cdx6500dot3DuplexMode.name: cdx6500dot3DuplexMode
cdx6500dot3DuplexMode.description: This parameter specifies whether this LAN port should run in either Half-Duplex or Full-Duplex mode.

cdx6500PPSTdot3PortTable.name: cdx6500PPSTdot3PortTable
cdx6500PPSTdot3PortTable.description: A table containing Ethernet statistics, one entry per 802.3 interface. All the statistics are defined using the syntax Counter as 32-bit wrap around counters. Thus, if an interface's hardware maintains these statistics in 16-bit counters, then the agent must read the hardware's counters frequently enough to prevent loss of significance, in order to maintain 32-bit counters in software.

cdx6500PPSTdot3PortEntry.name: cdx6500PPSTdot3PortEntry
cdx6500PPSTdot3PortEntry.description: An entry contains the 802.3 statistics for a particular interface.

cdx6500dot3StatsIfIndex.name: cdx6500dot3StatsIfIndex
cdx6500dot3StatsIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the 802.3 interface for which this entry contains management information. It is also the port number of the interface.

cdx6500dot3StatsPortType.name: cdx6500dot3StatsPortType
cdx6500dot3StatsPortType.description: The configured value of the Port type.

cdx6500dot3StatsRxShortFrames.name: cdx6500dot3StatsRxShortFrames
cdx6500dot3StatsRxShortFrames.description: This counter is incremented when the LAN port observes a receive or transmitted frame which is less than 18 bytes.

cdx6500dot3StatsRxCollisions.name: cdx6500dot3StatsRxCollisions
cdx6500dot3StatsRxCollisions.description: This counter is incremented when the LAN port observes collisions.

cdx6500dot3StatsRxLongFrames.name: cdx6500dot3StatsRxLongFrames
cdx6500dot3StatsRxLongFrames.description: This counter is incremented when the LAN port observes a frame that can not be forwarded because of excessive length.

cdx6500dot3StatsTxDiscards.name: cdx6500dot3StatsTxDiscards
cdx6500dot3StatsTxDiscards.description: This counter is incremented when the LAN port discards the frame because the transmit queue exceeds the maximum queue length.

cdx6500dot3StatsDataBytesRx.name: cdx6500dot3StatsDataBytesRx
cdx6500dot3StatsDataBytesRx.description: This counter is incremented for each data byte received by the LAN port.

cdx6500dot3StatsDataBytesTx.name: cdx6500dot3StatsDataBytesTx
cdx6500dot3StatsDataBytesTx.description: This counter is incremented for each data byte transmitted by the LAN port.

cdx6500dot3StatsPortStatus.name: cdx6500dot3StatsPortStatus
cdx6500dot3StatsPortStatus.description: Indicates the status of the LAN port. newvalDisabled : same functionality as 'disabled', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500dot3StatsLastStatReset.name: cdx6500dot3StatsLastStatReset
cdx6500dot3StatsLastStatReset.description: Time stamp when the statistics were last reset.

cdx6500dot3StatsClearStats.name: cdx6500dot3StatsClearStats
cdx6500dot3StatsClearStats.description: This is the command to reset the LAN port statistics.

cdx6500dot3StatsCommand.name: cdx6500dot3StatsCommand
cdx6500dot3StatsCommand.description: This is a control for the 802.3 port. enable : will enable the port. boot : will boot the port. disable : will disable the port.

cdx6500dot3Statsframesin.name: cdx6500dot3Statsframesin
cdx6500dot3Statsframesin.description: This counter is incremented for each frame received by the LAN port.

cdx6500dot3Statsframesout.name: cdx6500dot3Statsframesout
cdx6500dot3Statsframesout.description: This counter is incremented for each frame transmitted by the LAN port.

cdx6500dot3Statsfpsin.name: cdx6500dot3Statsfpsin
cdx6500dot3Statsfpsin.description: This stat specifies the number of frames per second received by the LAN port.

cdx6500dot3Statsfpsout.name: cdx6500dot3Statsfpsout
cdx6500dot3Statsfpsout.description: This stat specifies the number of frames per second transmitted by the LAN port.

cdx6500dot3Statshadiscards.name: cdx6500dot3Statshadiscards
cdx6500dot3Statshadiscards.description: This counter specifies the number of frames the HA discarded.
